{"id":8635,"date":"2025-09-23T05:51:27","date_gmt":"2025-09-23T05:51:27","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8635"},"modified":"2025-11-27T12:14:36","modified_gmt":"2025-11-27T12:14:36","slug":"kuala-lumpur","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/kuala-lumpur\/","title":{"rendered":"KUALA LUMPUR"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8827,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[108],"activities":[],"trip_types":[76],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[78],"class_list":["post-8635","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-truly-asia-malaysia","trip_types-customized-international-tour","tripcategory-customized-international-tour"],"packages_ids":[8636],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8635","price":65777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":5,"nights":4,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Discover the heart of Malaysia in its vibrant capital city, Kuala Lumpur. From the towering Petronas Twin Towers and bustling Bukit Bintang to the cultural charm of Batu Caves and Merdeka Square, KL offers a perfect mix of modern skyscrapers, rich heritage, and exciting shopping and dining experiences. A city that truly captures the spirit of <em>Truly Asia<\/em>.<br><br><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":"Return Economy Airfare BOM-BOM\nAccommodation mention or similar hotel. \nBB Basis (Breakfast Basis) \nMeet & Greet assistance at the airport and transfer directly to your hotel, Day at leisure \nReturn Airport& Inter Hotel Transfer by Pvt Basis. \nEnglish speaking driver cum guide assistance. \nTraditional welcome garland on arrival \nPer Person 1x 500 ml Water bottle during tours & transfers \nTravel goodies","cost_excludes":" Any meals other than those mentioned above included. \nAirfare \nVisa charges \nGST 5% \nAny portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all Items of personal nature. \nAny services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions. \nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle mal-Functions, political disturbances etc.","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. Do Indian travelers need a visa for Malaysia? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes, Indian passport holders need an eVisa or eNTRI to visit Malaysia.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. What are the must-visit attractions in Kuala Lumpur? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Petronas Twin Towers, Batu Caves, Merdeka Square, KL Tower, and Bukit Bintang shopping district.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. How many days are ideal for a Kuala Lumpur trip?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3 to 4 days are enough to explore the city\u2019s major highlights.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. What is the best time to visit Kuala Lumpur? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best months are March to September when the weather is relatively dry.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":374,"height":226,"file":"2025\/09\/kuala-lumpur-2.png","filesize":184245,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"kuala-lumpur-2-300x181.png","width":300,"height":181,"filesize":84733,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturec